Message.MsgText: ADMF0002E=ADMF0002E: Required parameter {0} is not found for command {1}.
Message.Explanation: One or more required parameters for the command is missing.
Message.UserResponse: Set all of the required parameters.

Message.MsgText: ADMF0005E=ADMF0005E: Command or command group {0} is not found.
Message.Explanation: The specified command or command group name is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the specified command or command group name is correct.

Message.MsgText: ADMF0008E=ADMF0008E: Command Framework failed to initialize or cannot create CommandMgr in {0} mode. Root cause is {1}.
Message.Explanation: Command Framework failed to initialize itself or cannot create CommandMgr in client, server or local mode.
Message.UserResponse: Check the call stack for root cause.

Message.MsgText: ADMF0001W=ADMF0001W: Command {0} targetObjectType is not set in the admin-command-def.xml file.
Message.Explanation: When the targetObject tag is allowed, the targetObjectType tag needs to be set in the CommandMetadata class. If the targetObject tag is not allowed, then command provider needs to set the targetObjectAllowed flag to false in the admin-command-def.xml file.
Message.UserResponse: Set the targetObjectType tag in the CommandMetadata class within the admin-command-def.xml file.

Message.MsgText: ADMF0003E=ADMF0003E: Invalid parameter value {0} for parameter {1} for command {2}.
Message.Explanation: The parameter value is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: A valid value is needed for the parameter.

Message.MsgText: ADMF0006E=ADMF0006E: Step {1} of command {0} is not found.
Message.Explanation: The step name is not valid for the specified command.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the specified step, command or command group name is correct.

Message.MsgText: ADMF0009E=ADMF0009E: Invalid parameter value {0} for parameter {1} for command {2}. Additional information: {3}
Message.Explanation: The parameter value is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: A valid value is needed for the parameter.

Message.MsgText: ADMF0004E=ADMF0004E: Invalid parameter name {0} for command {1}.
Message.Explanation: The specified parameter name is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: See the information center to determine the correct parameter name.

Message.Explanation: This command requires a target object.
Message.UserResponse: Specify the target object for the command.

Message.Explanation: User does not have the correct authority to run the command.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure user has correct authority or security role to perform the command.
